! Outline Editor Plugin

A ~TiddlyWiki plugin for creating and editing hierarchical outlines — structured documents composed of nested sections stored as individual tiddlers.

!! Overview

Each outline is a tiddler (tagged `Outline` by default) whose content is a tree of child tiddlers named by convention: `MyOutline(s1)`, `MyOutline(s1)(a)`, `MyOutline(s1)(a)(1)`, and so on. The plugin provides:

* A ''dashboard editor'' for managing the outline structure: adding, removing, renaming, and reordering sections without touching raw wikitext
* ''Display styles'' that control how sections render (outline, heading, list, plain), configurable per outline
* ''Special sections'' (e.g., table of contents) that pin to the top or bottom of the rendered output
* A ''revision/draft system'' for editing a copy of an outline without modifying the live version
* A ''compound archive'' that snapshots an entire outline tree into a single tiddler

!! Getting Started

# Install the plugin.
# Tag a tiddler with `Outline` (or your configured tag) and set its `text` field to `<<sections>>`.
# Click the ''edit outline'' toolbar button to open the dashboard.
# Use the dashboard to add sections, set a display style, and edit section content.

!! Configuration

Override these shadow tiddlers to customize the plugin for your wiki:

|!Tiddler |!Default |!Purpose |
|`$:/plugins/crosseye/outline/config/tag` |`Outline` |Tag that identifies outline tiddlers |
|`$:/plugins/crosseye/outline/config/draft-tag` |`OutlineDraft` |Tag for draft/revision copies |
|`$:/plugins/crosseye/outline/config/archive-prefix` |`$:/outline/archive/` |Title prefix for archived snapshots |
|`$:/plugins/crosseye/outline/config/button-filter` |//(matches tag)// |Filter controlling which tiddlers show the edit button |

!! Display Styles

The plugin ships with four display styles: ''Outline'', ''Heading'', ''List'', and ''Plain''. Each outline chooses one via its `display-style` field.

Add your own by creating a single tiddler tagged `$:/tags/Outline/DisplayStyle` with a `style-id` field, a `caption`, and a `\procedure` in the body whose name matches the `style-id`. The procedure renders a single section and has `<<marker>>` (the section label) and `<<section-type>>` (blank for normal sections, the suffix for special sections) available as variables. Set `disabled: yes` on any display style tiddler to suppress it from the dropdown and rendering.

!! Special Sections

Special sections are pinned to the top or bottom of the rendered outline, outside the normal section ordering. They are defined by configuration tiddlers rather than code changes.

''Built-in:'' Table of Contents (top, skipped by default).

To register a new special section, create a tiddler with:

* ''Tag:'' `$:/tags/Outline/SpecialSection/Top` or `$:/tags/Outline/SpecialSection/Bottom`
* ''Fields:''
** `suffix` — the parenthesized suffix used in tiddler titles (e.g., `history`)
** `caption` — display name shown in the dashboard
** `default` — `include` or `skip` (whether new outlines include it)
** `mandatory` — `yes` to show a warning banner when it's missing
** `content-type` — `manual` (user-edited) or `generated` (rendered by a procedure)
** `render-procedure` — procedure name to call when `content-type` is `generated`

Use the `list-before` / `list-after` fields on your config tiddlers, referencing other special section config tiddlers, to control ordering within the top or bottom group.

!! Revision / Draft Workflow

# Click ''Start Revision'' in the dashboard footer.
# A draft copy of the entire outline tree is created with a `draft-of-outline` field pointing back to the original.
# Edit the draft freely — all changes are isolated.
# Click ''Finish Revision'' to archive the current live version and promote the draft, or ''Discard'' to delete it.

Draft tiddlers are tagged with `OutlineDraft` (configurable) and a banner appears on the live outline linking to any in-progress revisions.

!! Extension Points

* ''Header panel:'' Override `$:/plugins/crosseye/outline/procedures/header-panel` to add fields above the section tree in the dashboard (e.g., policy number, description).
* ''New outline wizard:'' Override `$:/plugins/crosseye/outline/dashboard/new-outline-wizard` to customize the creation form.
* ''Edit button:'' Override `$:/plugins/crosseye/outline/ui/Buttons/edit-outline` to customize or replace the toolbar button.

!! Requirements

~TiddlyWiki >= 5.3.6
